&lt;table width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Structured Finance Team is responsible for the origination and credit underwriting of financial guaranty and credit insurance opportunities in a wide range of structured finance sectors including ABS, CLO, CRE, Fund Finance and other esoteric asset securitizations and financings. These transactions may contain elements of portfolio credit risk, corporate or financial institution credit risk, collateral value risk, interest rate risk or insurance-related risks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the development, writing and presentation of underwriting recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creation of spread sheet-based cash flow and financial models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the performance of due diligence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with rating agencies as part of shadow rating process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and compile industry trends/data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and development of new sectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Background&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 - 6 years’ experience, depending on qualifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undergraduate degree from a top-tier university, preferably with a focus on finance, accounting, or other quantitative discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General financial knowledge of fixed income capital markets (knowledge of structured finance useful but not required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to interact with clients, senior management and other departmental members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent computer literacy including Excel, Word and PowerPoint (cash flow modeling experience useful)Ability to work independently and as part of a small, cohesive team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;table width=&quot;733&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;733&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;733&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Annual base salary for the position is expected to be from $120,000 per year to $140,000 per year. The actual salary will depend on various factors, including but not limited to a candidate’s experience and credentials, salary expectations of applicable candidates, and other applicable market conditions. This position also provides applicable employee benefits, as well as eligibility for an annual discretionary bonus and long-term incentive awards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assured Guaranty is seeking a highly skilled and experienced corporate lawyer to join our dynamic legal team. The Counsel will be responsible for SEC filings and other public disclosures, securities laws matters, corporate governance, contract negotiation, strategic transactions, and rating agency matters. In addition, the Counsel will support aspects of the insurance regulatory function, including making filings on behalf of Assured Guaranty’s insurers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Counsel will work closely with the Deputy General Counsel with the objective of growing into a leading role with primary responsibility for Assured Guaranty’s public disclosures and other corporate matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparation of SEC filings, including proxy statements, 10-K&#39;s, 10-Qs and 8-Ks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legal research and advice, including with respect to the Securities Exchange Act and insurance regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparation of corporate governance documentation, including board and committee minutes and materials for quarterly Board of Directors meetings of Assured Guaranty Ltd. (the public parent holding company) and its insurance subsidiaries.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and negotiation of general corporate contracts (e.g., vendor agreements and license agreements).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legal support of the investor relations and marketing function, including reviewing press releases and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legal support of the human capital management function, including updating employee benefits plans and forms of offer letters and separation agreements and reviewing privacy and other policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legal advice and assistance with strategic transactions, including mergers, acquisitions and divestitures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assistance in preparation of insurance regulatory filings, including annual registration statement, enterprise risk report, corporate governance annual disclosure and other disclosures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legal support of rating agency activities, including reviewing contracts and materials for periodic updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table style=&quot;height: 349.719px;&quot; width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr style=&quot;height: 195.75px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 729.219px; height: 195.75px;&quot; width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Background&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least five to eight years of major law firm corporate and regulatory experience, ideally involving insurance company clients.&amp;nbsp; Additional experience in the law department of a major financial institution is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General corporate and securities law experience and understanding of the legal parameters and practices of corporate disclosure by public companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with securities laws, rules and regulations, particularly the Securities Act of 1933 and the Securities Exchange Act of 1934.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with financial, capital and credit markets business concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to work independently, gain the trust and confidence of coworkers, including in the production, financial reporting, risk, compliance and legal functions, and understand the business and workings of a financial services company with some level of comfort with numbers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core competencies and traits include: energetic; driven;

&lt;table width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assured Guaranty is seeking a Senior AI Software Engineer to build production-grade AI applications using our emerging agentic AI framework. This role focuses on translating business workflows into scalable, governed software that integrates AI agents, enterprise data, and existing platforms. This is a builder role—not research or experimentation. The expectation is to deliver working systems quickly, safely, and at enterprise scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working directly with business teams to translate workflows into production AI applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building AI-powered applications embedded directly in business workflows (document processing, analysis, decision support)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing multi-step AI workflows where agents reason, take actions, call tools, and iterate toward outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrating AI capabilities with enterprise systems (data platforms, APIs, internal tools)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using centralized platform services (orchestration, identity, logging, monitoring) to deliver scalable solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applying governance controls (auditability, guardrails, data protection) by design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leveraging AI-assisted development tools (e.g., Copilot, Claude Code) to accelerate delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in computer science, engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of software engineering experience, or equivalent practical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building production LLM-based applications (prompting, integration, evaluation)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to agent-based systems or multi-step AI workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of human-in-the-loop and validation patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong software development experience (Python, TypeScript, or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building APIs, services, and distributed systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating with structured and unstructured data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong quantitative and analytical skills to support credit and investment decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build within a centralized AI platform, leveraging shared services (identity, orchestration, logging, guardrails) rather than creating isolated solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with cloud-native development (AWS preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of secure coding practices and enterprise controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build systems that are auditable, traceable, and compliant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width=&quot;744&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
